### SwipeBuddy API Test Collection
### Prerequisites: Install the "REST Client" extension in VS Code to run these directly.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api/v1
@token = {{login.response.body.data.token}}

### ==========================================
### 1. AUTH MODULE
### ==========================================

### 1.1 Signup a new user
# @name signup
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Aditya Sharma",
  "email": "aditya@swipebuddy.local",
  "password": "password123",
  "phone": "9876543210"
}

### 1.2 Login (Sets the token variable automatically for subsequent requests)
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "aditya@swipebuddy.local",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 1.3 Login with invalid credentials (Negative Test Case)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "aditya@swipebuddy.local",
  "password": "wrongpassword"
}


### ==========================================
### 2. MASTER / LOOKUP MODULE
### ==========================================

### 2.1 Get Degrees
GET {{baseUrl}}/master/degrees

### 2.2 Get Positions
GET {{baseUrl}}/master/positions

### 2.3 Get Companies
GET {{baseUrl}}/master/companies

### 2.4 Get Institutions
GET {{baseUrl}}/master/institutions

### 2.5 Get Habits
GET {{baseUrl}}/master/habits

### 2.6 Get Amenities
GET {{baseUrl}}/master/amenities


### ==========================================
### 3. PROFILE MODULE
### ==========================================

### 3.1 Get My Profile (Requires Token)
GET {{baseUrl}}/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 3.2 Update My Profile (Requires Token)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "age": 24,
  "gender": "male",
  "city": "Bengaluru",
  "state": "Karnataka",
  "search_type": "flat",
  "is_published": true
}

### 3.3 Get My Profile again to verify updates
GET {{baseUrl}}/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 3.4 Get Profile by UUID
# Replace the UUID with a valid user id from your DB
GET {{baseUrl}}/profile/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000


### ==========================================
### 4. FLATS MODULE
### ==========================================

### 4.1 Get All Published Flats
GET {{baseUrl}}/flats

### 4.2 Create a Flat (Requires Token)
# @name createFlat
POST {{baseUrl}}/flats
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "address": "123 Startup Avenue",
  "city": "Bengaluru",
  "state": "Karnataka",
  "pincode": "560001",
  "latitude": 12.9716,
  "longitude": 77.5946,
  "furnishing_type": "furnished",
  "description": "Awesome 3BHK to share",
  "is_published": true
}

### 4.3 Get Flat By ID
# Replaces with the ID retrieved from createFlat
GET {{baseUrl}}/flats/{{createFlat.response.body.data.id}}

### 4.4 Create a Flat WITHOUT Token (Negative Test Case)
POST {{baseUrl}}/flats
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "address": "123 Startup Avenue",
  "city": "Bengaluru"
}
